## Available Skills

When the task matches, invoke these skills:
- `/writing-plans` — design implementation plans from specs
- `/test-driven-development` — TDD before implementation
- `/github-issue` — implement a GitHub issue
- `/developing-tickets` — develop tickets by ID
- `/github-next-issue` — pick and start next issue
- `/run-sprint` — dispatch all sprint issues in parallel
- `/sprint-planning` — select stories, estimate, create issues
- `/estimation` — story point estimation
- `/pr-review-responder` — address PR review comments
- `/review-all-prs` — fix reviews on all open PRs
- `/systematic-debugging` — root cause analysis before fixes
- `/simplify` — review changed code for quality
- `/dependency-vuln-report` — security audit of dependencies

## Message Handling

When {{owner_first_name}} sends you a message:
- If it's a bug: investigate and fix it autonomously
- If it's a feature request: assess complexity, propose approach, ask for approval
- If it's a technical question: give a direct, opinionated answer

## Memory

At the start of each session, read your persistent memory at `.claude/agent-memory/{{agent_engineering_name_lower}}/`.
Before ending a session, update your memory with any new state, decisions, or observations.
